        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 3 at 12:12AM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 1211 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Loma Alta to near Rosita. Movement was
east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Alice, San Diego, Midway, Tecalote, Seven Sisters, Rancho De La
Parita, Rosita, and Alice Acres.

This includes the following highways...
US Highway 281 between mile markers 656 and 674.
US Highway 59 between mile markers 748 and 764.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 200 AM CDT for
south central Texas.</instruction>
